00:18:19,322 --> 00:18:26,322
which is in neurons typically something like -70mV.

273
00:18:30,719 --> 00:18:32,058
So this is very interesting

274
00:18:32,515 --> 00:18:36,627
What I just showed you just using the numbers before that came from

275
00:18:36,837 --> 00:18:40,612
the Nernst equation and using this equation here

276
00:18:40,817 --> 00:18:45,842
to describe current flow of one branch and then over another branch

277
00:18:46,042 --> 00:18:47,671
over the third branch

278
00:18:48,040 --> 00:18:51,040
assuming that these other three current, only the three ions

279
00:18:51,282 --> 00:18:53,720
that determine the voltage across the membrane

280
00:18:53,920 --> 00:18:56,370
I now neglecting completely the capacitance

281
00:18:56,628 --> 00:19:01,128
because there is no voltage change so there is no capacitance current

282
00:19:03,073 --> 00:19:08,061
then I get this equation which is called the conductance equation

283
00:19:10,036 --> 00:19:14,336
which really describes the voltage across the membrane

284
00:19:14,541 --> 00:19:16,550
of a neuron at rest.

285
00:19:16,723 --> 00:19:18,548
The resting potential.

286
00:19:18,753 --> 00:19:21,753
Sometimes it is called E-rest of V-rest.

287
00:19:22,282 --> 00:19:26,707
And I just told you that it is -70mV inside the cell.

288
00:19:26,885 --> 00:19:30,898
this means that at rest, without doing anything

289
00:19:31,082 --> 00:19:34,719
before you get a spike, before you get a synaptic potential

290
00:19:34,933 --> 00:19:36,846
just at rest.

291
00:19:38,083 --> 00:19:41,433
When all of the currents balance each other you get net current

292
00:19:41,653 --> 00:19:48,316
so there is no voltage change, the inside of the cell is about 70mV

