00:19:48,515 --> 00:19:52,265
more negative compared to the outside of the cell.

294
00:19:53,221 --> 00:19:56,846
So neurons sits because of this gradiance

295
00:19:57,051 --> 00:20:00,613
of concentration of the three ions that I mentioned

296
00:20:00,809 --> 00:20:06,697
all the neurons in the world, sit in a negative potential

297
00:20:06,900 --> 00:20:10,213
inside versus outside, and this is the reference potential

298
00:20:10,415 --> 00:20:12,953
for all the rest of the potentials

299
00:20:13,149 --> 00:20:15,567
for all the rest of the electrical activity

300
00:20:15,662 --> 00:20:16,717
that I will speaking about.

301
00:20:17,016 --> 00:20:21,366
So if I speak about the spike, it will start from -70mV

302
00:20:21,578 --> 00:20:24,215
and then jump to the positive direction.

303
00:20:24,396 --> 00:20:26,096
If I will speak about the synaptic potential

304
00:20:26,275 --> 00:20:30,337
they will start from -70mV, they could be more positive

305
00:20:30,534 --> 00:20:34,147
or more negative, but all relative to -70mV.

306
00:20:34,347 --> 00:20:39,554
So this -70, this

307
00:20:39,713 --> 00:20:42,988
the resting potential is really the baseline, the reference potential

308
00:20:43,177 --> 00:20:45,327
for all other development of other types of signals

309
00:20:45,528 --> 00:20:48,203
the spikes and the synaptic potential.

310
00:20:48,396 --> 00:20:54,846
So this is really the essence of the electrical basis

311
00:20:55,059 --> 00:20:58,272
for neuronal activity.

312
00:20:58,664 --> 00:21:01,601
And maybe I will end by saying the following

313
00:21:01,817 --> 00:21:04,067
this part I will end by saying the following

314
00:21:04,246 --> 00:21:08,083
that the trick of neurons, really the trick of neurons

315
00:21:08,265 --> 00:21:12,415
is to be able to change the conductances very fast

316
00:21:12,612 --> 00:21:16,812
so if I could change the potassium conductance very fast

317
00:21:17,046 --> 00:21:20,396
I will get a more negative potential inside

318
00:21:20,655 --> 00:21:22,295
because of this negativity here.

319
00:21:22,619 --> 00:21:26,806
If I succeed to change the sodium conductance very fast

320
00:21:26,993 --> 00:21:32,718
I will get a more positive voltage inside.

321
00:21:32,919 --> 00:21:35,919
That's the trick of neurons, the fast trick of neurons

322
00:21:36,126 --> 00:21:40,864
to change potentials, both synaptic and spiking

323
00:21:41,068 --> 00:21:44,068
by changing these conductances.

324
00:21:45,184 --> 00:21:47,704
But what makes these conductances change

325
00:21:47,932 --> 00:21:50,932
that's the trick of the membrane of the neurons

326
00:21:51,131 --> 00:21:53,720
which is very unique and this is of course

