00:21:59,624 --> 00:22:03,262
of the conductances of the membrane to change

329
00:22:03,436 --> 00:22:07,711
and thus generate new voltages, different voltages

330
00:22:07,928 --> 00:22:10,928
the synaptic potentials and the spiking potentials.

331
00:22:11,241 --> 00:22:14,741
So let me summarize this introductory part

332
00:22:14,937 --> 00:22:18,462
to the electrical activity of neurons

333
00:22:18,649 --> 00:22:21,649
I just said that the membrane ion channels

334
00:22:23,719 --> 00:22:25,769
the membrane ion channels

335
00:22:25,987 --> 00:22:29,600
are the poles are the conductances when open

336
00:22:29,828 --> 00:22:34,765
that enable the flow of currents from the inside to the outside

337
00:22:34,971 --> 00:22:36,896
or from the outside to the inside

338
00:22:37,080 --> 00:22:38,455
across the membrane.

339
00:22:38,627 --> 00:22:42,577
And I told you that the three key ions that play a role

340
00:22:42,755 --> 00:22:46,930
in determining the potential of the membranes

341
00:22:47,144 --> 00:22:49,644
of biological membranes, of neuronal membrane

342
00:22:49,860 --> 00:22:53,848
are the sodium, the potassium, and the chloride.

343
00:22:54,061 --> 00:22:56,276
There are other ions, for example the calcium

344
00:22:56,302 --> 00:22:58,502
but for the resting potential at least

345
00:22:58,683 --> 00:23:01,683
these are the three most important ions.

346
00:23:02,239 --> 00:23:08,302
And what really makes this difference of concentration in ions

347
00:23:08,510 --> 00:23:10,973
enable to generate voltage

348
00:23:11,185 --> 00:23:13,410
is their capability to cross the membrane

349
00:23:13,614 --> 00:23:19,439
and this gradient of voltage skeptured by the Nernst equation

350
00:23:19,655 --> 00:23:23,655
as a battery, so I can speak about the three batteries that determine

351
00:23:23,873 --> 00:23:28,185
the overall voltage at rest and also for other potentials.

352
00:23:28,385 --> 00:23:32,187
We saw the ENA, the battery of the sodium,

353
00:23:32,421 --> 00:23:36,521
the Nernst potential for sodium, the battery for the potassium,

354
00:23:36,730 --> 00:23:38,685
and the battery for the chloride.

355
00:23:39,006 --> 00:23:42,381
And I showed in this conductance equation that overall you have

356
00:23:42,590 --> 00:23:47,952
some kind of a balance between the three batteries and their

357
00:23:48,150 --> 00:23:50,638
corresponding conductances.

358
00:23:50,819 --> 00:23:54,394
So the conductance of the branch that has the conductance

359
00:23:54,594 --> 00:23:57,802
of the sodium and its batery,

360
00:23:58,077 --> 00:24:01,015
the branch that has the potassium conductance and its battery

361
00:24:01,243 --> 00:24:03,131
and the chloride conductance and its battery

362
00:24:03,314 --> 00:24:06,314
the combined equation, which is the conductance equation

363
00:24:06,670 --> 00:24:10,720
determines the end result of the resting potential.

364
00:24:10,928 --> 00:24:15,741
I showed you that the resting potential, the typical neuron is around -70mV

365
00:24:15,933 --> 00:24:18,933
negative inside compared to the outside,

366
00:24:19,507 --> 00:24:23,544
which by the way means that the dominant conductance

