00:24:23,923 --> 00:24:28,448
at rest is the potassium conductance, and the chloride as well,

368
00:24:28,664 --> 00:24:32,464
but the potassium conductance really determines mostly

369
00:24:32,673 --> 00:24:36,186
the resting potential because it is the potassium conductance

370
00:24:36,430 --> 00:24:37,718
which is associated with

371
00:24:37,917 --> 00:24:40,606
a negative battery of the potassium

372
00:24:40,832 --> 00:24:43,182
it is the one that is the most dominant

373
00:24:43,370 --> 00:24:49,933
meaning that at rest, the sodium is not very conductive

